
[1]helplessness

   HELP'LESSNESS, n. Want of strength or ability; inability; want of means
   in one's self to obtain relief in trouble, or to accomplish one's
   purposes or desires.

   It is the tendency of sickness to reduce our extravagant
   self-estimation, by exhibiting our solitary helplessness.
